The paper deals with coalgebras, which are a topic in theoretical computer science and logic. The concept of well-pointedness is closely related to the study of coalgebras, and the paper provides a new description of the final coalgebra and the initial algebra. The paper also discusses examples such as automata, graphs, and labeled transition systems, which are commonly studied in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
